      • traverseStreamGraphAndGenerateHashes

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,byte[]> traverseStreamGraphAndGenerateHashes(StreamGraph streamGraph)
        Returns a map with a hash for each StreamNode of the StreamGraph. The hash is used as the JobVertexID in order to identify nodes across job submissions if they didn't change.

        The complete StreamGraph is traversed. The hash is either computed from the transformation's user-specified id (see StreamTransformation.getUid()) or generated in a deterministic way.

        The generated hash is deterministic with respect to:

        • node-local properties (like parallelism, UDF, node ID),
        • chained output nodes, and
        • input nodes hashes
        指定者:
        traverseStreamGraphAndGenerateHashes 在接口中 StreamGraphHasher
        返回:
        A map from StreamNode.id to hash as 16-byte array.

      • generateNodeHash

        private boolean generateNodeHash(StreamNode node,
                                 org.apache.flink.shaded.guava18.com.google.common.hash.HashFunction hashFunction,
                                 java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,byte[]> hashes,
                                 boolean isChainingEnabled)
        Generates a hash for the node and returns whether the operation was successful.
        参数:
        node - The node to generate the hash for
        hashFunction - The hash function to use
        hashes - The current state of generated hashes
        返回:
        true if the node hash has been generated. false, otherwise. If the operation is not successful, the hash needs be generated at a later point when all input is available.
        抛出:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If node has user-specified hash and is intermediate node of a chain

      • generateNodeLocalHash

        private void generateNodeLocalHash(StreamNode node,
                                   org.apache.flink.shaded.guava18.com.google.common.hash.Hasher hasher,
                                   int id)
        Applies the Hasher to the StreamNode (only node local attributes are taken into account). The hasher encapsulates the current state of the hash.

        The specified ID is local to this node. We cannot use the StreamNode.id, because it is incremented in a static counter. Therefore, the IDs for identical jobs will otherwise be different.
